data.value: A constraint on the uniqueness of a set of columns. Equivalent to a 'UNIQUE' or 'PRIMARY KEY' in the SQL Standard.

data.name: Neumont.Tools.RelationalModels.ConceptualDatabase.CheckConstraint.Description
data.value: Equivalent to a table-level or domain 'CHECK' clause in the SQL Standard.

data.value: The number of characters in a CHARACTER, CHARACTER VARYING, or CHARACTER LARGE OBJECT, or the number of bytes in a BINARY LARGE OBJECT.

data.name: Neumont.Tools.RelationalModels.ConceptualDatabase.PredefinedDataType/Precision.Description
data.value: The maximum number of decimal digits in a NUMERIC or DECIMAL, or the maximum number of binary digits in the significand (mantissa) of a FLOAT.

data.name: Neumont.Tools.RelationalModels.ConceptualDatabase.PredefinedDataType/Scale.Description
data.value: The maximum number of decimal digits after the decimal point in a NUMERIC or DECIMAL.
